
A basic test script to test in a stand-alone way 
the CRAB Data Discovery based on DBS, is:

./testDBS_CRAB.py <owner> <dataset> <comma separated list of datatiers>

The others python modules it uses are:
 o DataDiscovery.py  --> uses DBSInfo
 o DBSInfo.py --> DBS query using HTTP-CGI for getDatasetContents and DBSXMLDump for getDatasetProvenance
 o DBSXMLHandler.py --> read DBS XML files

The code uses:
  - getDatasetContents API from HTTP/CGI
  - getDatasetProvenance API from  PHEDEX/Utilities/DBSXMLDump
 
so you still need to use and configure PHEDEX environment.
You need to configure the DBSInfo.py to point at your PHEDEX installation.

